ats, up from 11 in 2019, while the SNP would lose 30 seats, falling from 48 to 18. Reform UK would win three seats, with Nigel Farage returned as MP for Clacton.The Labour victory would earn the largest majority won by any single party since 1832, when the Whigs romped home to a majority of 224 following the extension of the franchise under the Great Reform Act.05:03 PM BSTThird MRP poll predicts historic Tory defeatA third MRP poll has predicted a historic Conservative defeat at the general election.The YouGov survey of 42,758 voters predicted a 212-seat Labour majority, with the party winning a total of 431 constituencies.The poll put the Tories on 102 seats, the Liberal Democrats on 72 and Reform UK on three.Jeremy Hunt, the Chancellor, Grant Shapps, the Defence Secretary, and Gillian Keegan, the education secretary, were all projected to lose their seats.The SNP are forecast to drop 30 seats to 18 and the Greens will gain one, reaching two MPs.Final YouGov MRP shows Labour on course for historic election victoryLabour: 431 (+229 from GE2019 result)Con: 102 (-263)Lib Dem: 72 (+61)SNP: 18 (-30)Reform UK: 3 (+3)Plaid: 3 (-1)Green: 2 (+1)Fieldwork: 19 June - 2 Julyhttps://t.co/JxacgEVIPW pic.twitter.com/g8G2mtbGTn— YouGov (@YouGov) July 3, 202404:52 PM BSTFarage defends appearing with ChisoraNigel Farage has defended his decision to appear alongside boxer Derek Chisora at a campaign event in Clacton, Essex.Asked about Mr Chisora’s conviction for assaulting a woman in 2010, the Reform UK leader said: “You know what? You show me someone who’s lived a perfect life and never been in trouble.“With these young kids here, he’s a fantastic role model.“He’s got a huge following in the country and yeah, he is a good role model – imperfect as we all are.”Derek Chisora and Nigel Farage together in Clacton, Essex, on Wednesday - ANDY RAIN/EPA-EFE/Shutterstock04:44 PM BSTRecipe for Sunak’s 4kg ‘election pie’ revealedRishi Sunak’s butcher has revealed the recipe for the Prime Mini